OL,3,CNew cancer centre given the go-ahead
OL,5,FAt the moment, cancer patients are
OL,6,Ftreated in a 'cramped' unit in a
OL,7,Fbuilding that is no longer fit for
OL,8,Fpurpose.
OL,10,FDr George Findlay said: "Sadly the
OL,11,Fdemand for cancer care is going up
OL,12,Fquite considerably.
OL,14,F"Our current cancer centre is really
OL,15,Fquite small and outdated, so this new
OL,16,Fcancer centre will almost give us
OL,17,Fseven times the footprint, three times
OL,18,Fthe clinical space and a much better
OL,19,Fenvironment for our staff to deliver
OL,20,Fgreat care for patients."
